    <p>Epi­gram has re­leased the third book in its graphic novel line-up for the year – Re­al­ity Bitch­slap by Malaysian Arif Rafhan. It is in­spired by real events that oc­curred dur­ing his and his friends’ trav­els. Arif is a comic artist, pre-pro­duc­tion vi­su­aliser, mu­ral artist and teacher.</p>
    <p>Pur­chase it at shop.epi­gram­books.sg/ prod­ucts/re­al­ity-bitch­slap</p>
    <p>$18.90</p>
    <p>Sto­ries: Let’s Con­nect!</p>
    <p>In this event by the Speak Good English Move­ment, au­thors and sto­ry­tellers read sto­ries for chil­dren and adults. Among the chil­dren’s sto­ries are Lit­tle God­wit Finds His Wings and The Lit­tle Sin­ga­pore Book. Sto­ries that are suit­able for teens and adults in­clude The Never Mind Girl by Rose­marie So­ma­iah and The Looker by Jon Gre­sham.</p>
    <p>View it on www.face­book.com/ speak­good­english­move­ment Wed, 4pm</p>
    <p>Free</p>


